reviewText:
Old video and not worth my Wife's time either. She asked me to review it. At first I confused this with another video but I am now reviewing the correct video. After watching this thing I felt like I had stepped into an 80s vortex.
Nuff said.
Thanks for your time,
M. Merritt

Thank you for re-sending our order for Extreme At-Home Workout video. My wife received this DVD in perfect condition with no scratches, cracks, or cover damage at all. she likes that it has 10 minute workouts to fit her busy life as a mother of two. She plans on trying it out and recommends this movie workout to her sister. Thanks for all your trouble(s) you, (Amazon) and the seller(s) went through to help me receive me purchase. I am a very happy customer and I definitely will come back for more.
these cd's are not worth ur money poor quailty poor camera effects and the instructers are horrible don't waste ur money

This set of DVDs is awesome kick for your buck. Well designed workouts with good explanation, good form, pleasant music. Nothing extream, everything accurate, precise and safe. If you look for some veriety in your workouts, I recommend you this set. Some martial arts conditioning, some Pilates, some aerobics - sweat and have fun.
